        <article class="blog-post">
            <img src="assets/images/Image2.jpg" alt="Image-2">
            <div class="blog">
                <h3>AI-driven cyber attacks to be the norm within a year, say security leadersCyber</h3>
                <h4>Cyber Attack AI Driven</h4>
                <p>
                    Recently AI has been constantly looked at the newest weapon to fight cyber attacks
                    with the ease of programing and algorithyms it is being used in offence and defence in the
                    cyber security battle. On that note AI is also starting to be used to create cyber attacksit is
                    enhancing the way cyber criminals are using to their benefit this new technology.
                    The pressure is on security leaders to do more with less, and so the rise of the use of AI to enhance cyber attacks could not have come at a worse time,
                    said Andy Still, CTO & Co-Founder, Netacea.
                    AI's power and low barrier to entry means that it will be used in many ways, including cyberattacks. While it's heartening that so many leaders recognise
                    the everyday threat they face from AI, there are gaps in understanding where the most damaging threats are coming from. In the arms race between offensive
                    and defensive AI, it's important to recognise that AI will be used anywhere it can be, and they need to respond in kind.



                </p>
            </div>
